# Walkthrough: Unified UI & Typography Overhaul

We have successfully transformed the Sprint Relay Debugger with a premium, high-contrast light-mode aesthetic and a fully refined typography system.

## Key Accomplishments

### 1. Typography & Readability Overhaul
We addressed the "awful" readability of stylized headers by implementing a more balanced typographic system:
- **Title Case Transition**: Switched from aggressive all-caps to professional Title Case for major headers and section labels.
- **Balanced Weights**: Moved from `font-black` to `font-bold` for better clarity at smaller sizes and to avoid visual "blurring".
- **Tracking Optimization**: Reduced extreme letter spacing (tracking) to improve word recognition and scannability.
- **Clean Sub-headers**: Removed italics from instructional text and secondary info to ensure crisp legibility.

### 2. Unified TaskCard Component
- **Shared Architecture**: A single, robust [TaskCard.tsx](file:///c:/Users/Admin/Desktop/Sprintdebug/sprint-relay/src/components/dashboard/TaskCard.tsx) now powers all task displays in the app.
- **Improved Context**: Highly readable tags for **Module** and **Screen** provide a quicker overview of task metadata.
- **Simplified Actions**: Removed redundant buttons to declutter the interface.

### 3. Branding & Theme
- **Navy Accent (`#1D3557`)**: Successfully transitioned the entire UI from purple/indigo to a professional navy blue theme.
- **High Contrast**: Optimized all badges, dots, and borders for an accessible light-mode experience.

## View-by-View Refinements

- **Daily Meeting**: Refreshed headers for Personnel Assembly, Global Backlog, and Sync Protocol.
- **Personnel View**: Cleaned up the Mission Backlog and Active Protocol sections.
- **Squad Planner**: Modernized the Next Sprint Planning interface for better clarity during high-intensity planning.
- **Historical & Recap**: Ensured consistency in archive and review views with refined table headers and legends. Purged high-intensity 'font-black' from summary statistics and sort controls to maintain a professional look.

